  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599.73 sitting just below the massive +12.4B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher while providing buying support on dips toward 6580 where they hold significant short gamma. The regime flip into PIN with 22.5B total GEX creates a powerful mean-reversion environment, with the 6605-6610 gamma cluster acting as a major ceiling and the GEX flip at 6624 marking the upper boundary of dealer stabilization. Key inflection points are 6580 (max negative gamma support) and 6605 (max positive gamma resistance), with dealers likely already hedging the approaching gamma wall through pre-emptive selling.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 6580-6610 with strong resistance at current levels.",
